%% Source: VIDEO_WALKTHROUGH_SCRIPT.md — Part 2, [SHOW DIAGRAM: Request Flow Step-by-Step]
%% The five-step lifecycle of a single log entry from client to searchable index

sequenceDiagram
    participant CLI  as curl / simulator / your app
    participant GW   as API Gateway :8080
    participant IGS  as Log Ingest Service :8090
    participant DRAW as raw_logs (log_aggregator DB)
    participant BG   as Background Thread (Ingest @Async)
    participant QS   as Log Query Service :8091
    participant DIAW as indexed_logs (log_query_db)
    participant DASH as Dashboard (browser)

    Note over CLI,GW: STEP 1 — Client sends a log

    CLI->>GW: POST http://localhost:8080/ingest/log<br/>{ "level": "ERROR", "message": "Payment failed", ... }

    Note over GW,IGS: STEP 2 — API Gateway routes it

    GW->>GW: sees /ingest/** → asks Eureka where LOG-INGEST-SERVICE is
    GW->>IGS: forward request to :8090

    Note over IGS,DRAW: STEP 3 — Ingest Service saves it, returns immediately

    IGS->>IGS: validates log level, creates LogEntry object
    IGS->>DRAW: saves to raw_logs table ✓ (durable — log never lost)
    IGS-->>CLI: 200 OK  ← returns IMMEDIATELY without waiting for indexing
    IGS-)BG: fires async background task (non-blocking)

    Note over BG,DIAW: STEP 4 — Indexing happens in the background

    BG->>GW: POST /query/index  (goes back through Gateway)
    GW->>QS: routes to Log Query Service :8091
    QS->>QS: builds searchable_text<br/>"payment-service error payment failed"<br/>(source_app + level + message, lowercased)
    QS->>DIAW: saves to indexed_logs ✓

    Note over DASH,DIAW: STEP 5 — Dashboard searches

    DASH->>GW: POST /query/search  "find logs matching 'payment failed'"
    GW->>QS: routes /query/** to Log Query Service
    QS->>DIAW: SELECT * FROM indexed_logs<br/>WHERE searchable_text ILIKE '%payment failed%'<br/>ORDER BY timestamp DESC
    DIAW-->>QS: matching rows (paginated)
    QS-->>DASH: JSON response → dashboard renders results
